                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <head>No. 30.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tree</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 17, 1887</date>. (Received March
                        4.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 203.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 186, I met Mr. Charles M.
                    Reels, the burgomaster of Brussels, last evening at a ball at the palace, and
                    had a talk with him about the proposed visit of the Gate City Guard, of Atlanta,
                    to Brussels next summer. He told me that he would do all he could to make their
                    visit an agreeable one, and that they would be formally received at the <hi
                        rend="italic">Hôtel de Ville</hi>, which will be a distinguished municipal
                    compliment to them.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lambert Tree.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
